Aim: Use basic networking commands in Linux (ping, tracert, nslookup, netstat, ip, ifconfig, dig, route)

Hardware/Software required: Command Prompt OR Terminal

1. ifconfig
2. ping
3. tracepath <server name> --- tracepath google.com
4. traceroute <server name> --- traceroute google.com
5. host <server name> --- host google.com
6. nslookup <server name> --- nslookup google.com
7. netstat OR netstat -an
8. ip
9. dig <server name> --- dig google.com
